1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Hello LinkedIn team,

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,000
My name is Cristian, and today I’m presenting MetricMind.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:22,000
MetricMind is a web intelligence platform designed to help users analyze
and activate digital presence signals through authorized platform connections.

4
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Users can access the platform either by creating their own credentials
or by signing in with Google.

5
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:40,000
In this demonstration,
I will continue using Google authentication.

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Once inside, the user can start by entering any website they want to analyze,
which allows MetricMind to identify publicly available digital signals associated with that domain.

7
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:07,000
At this stage, we see the main analysis panel.

8
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Initially, the platform highlights available integrations, such as Meta,
which will be used in future steps.

9
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:27,000
After entering a website, MetricMind performs a web intelligence scan
to detect the brand’s digital presence.

10
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:37,000
This includes identifying publicly available signals such as social media profiles
associated with the website.

11
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:47,000
The goal is to provide users with a structured view of their digital footprint,
and prepare the environment for authorized connections.

12
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:57,000
Once relevant signals are identified, the user can proceed to connect their accounts,
including LinkedIn, through secure authorization.

13
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:08,000
At this point, the LinkedIn connection option becomes available.

14
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:20,000
The user is then redirected to LinkedIn to sign in and authorize the application
through OAuth.

15
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:31,000
This ensures that all interactions with LinkedIn are fully compliant
and based on explicit user consent.

16
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:41,000
After authorization is completed, MetricMind securely receives the necessary permissions
to access basic profile data and enable further actions within the platform.

17
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:48,000
Once connected, we can see the initial results based on LinkedIn data.

18
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:54,000
The platform activates signal detection and enables interaction features
such as content publishing.

19
00:02:54,000 --> 00:03:00,000
At this moment, organization-level access is still restricted,
which is precisely why we are applying for the Community Management API.

20
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:05,000
This approval will allow us to expand these capabilities
to organization pages.

21
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:18,000
Now, we proceed to create a post directly from MetricMind.

22
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:32,000
The content is published through the LinkedIn integration,
and once the post is live, we copy its URL.

23
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:46,000
This URL is then used in the tracking section,
where MetricMind begins monitoring engagement signals.

24
00:03:46,000 --> 00:04:00,000
The platform tracks interactions such as comments and activity related to the post,
providing a structured view of engagement.

25
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:14,000
All data shown here is obtained through authorized interactions
and user-provided inputs.

26
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Finally, this demonstrates how MetricMind connects web intelligence
with social platform activation in a compliant and user-driven way.

27
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:43,000
Thank you for your time,
and we look forward to your approval.
